																		RULES UPDATES THREAD
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183614" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1560209156 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Jun 2019 23:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4277082">
									

<p>Special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1422059); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1422059&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1561423297" alt="MayD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1422059)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1422059); return false;">MayD</a></span> for proposing and then writing up the ruleset for this contest!</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Foundation does <em>NOT</em> count as a GOI for this purpose.</li>
<li>More than two GOIs may be used, but both articles must focus on the same two.</li>
<li>All times are in EST!</li>
<li>All entries that dip to the deletion mark will be subject to normal deletion practices.</li>
<li>If an article is deleted, <em>you can not resubmit it or submit a new one</em>.</li>
<li>Clarified rules about how many pages a team can have.</li>
<li>Added the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-12065263/collaboration-contest#post-4277955">Looking for Team Thread</a> for prospective entrants to find partners!</li>
<li>Added the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-12140200/collaboration-contest-attribution-request-thread">Attribution Request thread</a> for contest entrants to request that the attribution metadata for their entries be updated!</li>
</ul>

